The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sania sails into final of Challenger
                                                     Sania sails into final of Challenger
          
	New Delhi: Sania Mirza overcame a fighting Meng Yuan in a three-setter to earn a shot at the singles title in the $50,000 ITF Challenger event in Lexington, United States Saturday.         
	The second seed Indian defeated the sixth seed Chinese 6-1, 4-6, 6-4 in the semi-final of the hard court event.         
	Sania will now fight it out with top-seed French Julie Coin, who defeated Kai-Chen Chang of Chinese Taipei 6-2, 6-4 in her last-four match.         
	Earlier, on Saturday Sania advanced to the semi-finals after Lindsay Lee-Waters withdrew.         
	The second seed Indian was leading 5-2 in the first set when her American opponent opted out of the quarter final contest. Sania is in the United States preparing for the gruelling hard court season ahead. (PtI)                                                                                                                       
